<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-03-28T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-03-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="61" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Air Armaments/234:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Acting Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-28T19:00:00-05:00">March 28,
                                    1933—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>313. Your 584, March 22, 6 p.m., and 589, March 23, 8 p.m.<note n="11" xml:id="d61fn11">Latter not printed.</note> We see no objection to
                            the draft joint statement and approve of your proposed method of
                            handling the matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>